cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CV 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with traffic control in an edge network. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the proposed algorithm is based on label-less learning. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible category as the paper deals with offloading data to the cloud. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also possible as the paper deals with designing an algorithm for controlling traffic in a system. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions real-time emotion recognition as an example of an intelligent application.
